<br>
Since I'm posting, let me make a few random comments... Regarding the &quot;secret handshake&quot;: although this does seem like a bug to me (albeit a well-entrenched bug), I just consider it compensation for the fact that EQ rogues can't steal from vendors. After all, a &quot;real&quot; rogue wouldn't have to worry about whether a shopkeeper liked him, would he?<br>
<br>
I think an earlier speed increase while sneaking is an excellent idea, and lvl 41 is the perfect time for it, since rogues currently have nothing to look forward to but HPs between 40 and 50. I also think that cancellable illusions are essential (why can't all buffs be cancelled, anyway?), and hiding/sneaking across zone borders and linkdeath would be very nice.<br>
<br>
Finally, what ever happened to the ID/BS issue? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aerimus>Aerimus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/01 9:59:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2090.topic&index=44>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Talk Item List - Absor</span><hr size=1> New Locked Doors...<br>
<br>
Currently there are 2 types<br>
<br>
Unpickable...Doors to areas where verant doesn't want to negate the effort that should be required to get in<br>
<br>
Pickable... Places where a rogue is either required or very helpful, usually with something quite nice behind em<br>
<br>
New doors should be scattered over various dungeons and towns in places like peoples homes (makes sense right) and odd corners and passageways in dungeons (places where you don't really have to go)<br>
These doors should be pickable but should also be able to be opened by force, either magical or brute strength.  Forcing the door should agro mobs in a quite small radius<br>
<br>
The provision that said doors only be in places where you don't have to go is because it would make travel impossible in many places without a rogue if you were not in a group that could fight your way past certain points.  If additional doors were placed at key points you had to move through most hurt would be single players trying to move through invis to join groups in progress.<br>
<br>
Certain important places could be guarded by the new doors but not very many.  Mostly these doors should guard easier routes through dungeons (meaning rogueless groups would have to choose between fighting their way through or taking somewhat more difficult paths)<br>
<br>
This would provide another use for rogues scouting and would provide rogues with an interesting way to train their skill rather than sitting at a door for hours opening and closing it.  <br>
<br>
It would slightly inconvenience others moving through certain areas by requiring them to a) have a rogue b) take a slightly longer or more dangerous route if moving invis c) fight a few mobs at key points<br>
<br>
Would provide a few points were rogues made the trip a lot easier rather than a little (but less so than say HS keys)<br>
<br>
This would be most appropriate in new zones rather than existing ones clearly<br>
<br>
How to do it at each door is an npc that is completely invis, with a few hp, that is social with surrounding mobs but has a small call for help radius, that changes the state of the door when it dies, named door.  Picking the lock would leave the npc but would negate the need to kill it<br>
<br>
What I'd really like to see is all our rogue skills mean something in everyday play in more situations. This is the same reason why rogue hide should require a different spell (gained at the same lvl) to see through it.  This wouldn't prevent casters from seeing rogues but would lessen the % chance that a caster would have a spell up to see a rogue thus making our invis mean something in vs players on a pvp server where 8 of the classes have invis/see invis and the 6 classes (4 of which are in classes that are less played on average) which cannot can get items that allow them to at least see invis <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub76.ezboard.com/ulenilya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>lenilya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/01 11:24:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2090.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Talk Item List - Absor</span><hr size=1> Fletched thorwing weapons...<br>
