<br>
<i>Five percent less experience required to level than any other class besides warriors.</i><br>
<br>
...which, until 2 patches ago (I think that's right, so many patches, so many months) was a disadvantage, as we recieved less of a share of the xp while in groups ^^<br>
<br>
<i>D isciplines added.</i><br>
<br>
And only 3 are really useful.  Nimble, (Counterattack is useless due to the high recycle time), Deadeye (until we get duellist), and Duellist.  You could remove all the other disc's from our list, and i'd never notice.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Monks- Voiddance (immunity to melee damage, from all sides), Stone stance (fast recharge rate, good damage reduction), also have the duellist style disc as Innerflame.<br>
<br>
Warriors- Defensive (what can i say?  this is the reason that Velious mobs are able to be killed.  You are REQUIRED to use warriors to tank Velious ubers), Fortitude (again, complete immunity to melee damage), also have the duellist style disc with Fell Strike (and additional methods of dealing a lot of damage fast with Mighty strike, Charge, and agressive/precision)<br>
<br>
So, it's not like rogues really got some huge advantage. Duellist is kinda fun for the uber stabs, but it's hardly as class defining as Defensive, or the pulling tools that monks have, stonestance and void dance.  Imho, Rogues would have greatly benefitted by a discipline along the lines of agressive or precision, where we deal 30% more damage over the next 3 mins, but take more damage if we screw up too.<br>
<br>
<i>Pick Pockets level cap raised.</i><br>
<br>
And strangely, it's no where near to what it used to be...  We should still be able to pick magic items off of mobs, with certain mobs being flagged as un-pickable, and also unable to pick no drop items.<br>
<br>
<i>Poisons revamped.</i><br>
<br>
And are still nearly totally worthless due to their implimentation. Muscle lock poisons are a joke, they wear off nearly as soon as you use them, and at 10 plat a pop, not including failures... Most poisons worth anything require hours and hours of camping greens that no one camps, so we can't buy the components off of players, we have to spend all that time ourselves.  And for what? there are very few good poisons, and no poisons are good enough to require hours and hours of tedium.  I challenge anyone to go out and get a stack of 20 heartsting scorpion venoms. haha, especially without tracking ^^<br>
<br>
<br>
And for all that, while all those items are improvements, the rogue class also had the furthest to go to become a "viable" class in EQ.  Come on, I would have a hard time believing that even Kendrick forgets this.  While the rogue class has seen a lot of positive attention, the only 3 really big things are: Evade (now nerfed by a fair amount), Increased damage tables, Sneak/hide improvements.  For all the griping that you see rangers do, Rangers started out incredibly butch.  They just didn't see any upgrades, while warriors/paladins/SK's got bonuses, and paladins/SK's soon fell by the wayside, not as badly in kunark as is true in velious though.  Defensive is too necessary a tool when you consider mobs quadding for 850's, and normal blue mobs hitting for 180-250's.  Heh, nothing surprises you more than Assassinating a mob that's hitting the tank for 170's (icewall dwarves).<br>
<br>
Again, not saying that rogues needed improvement, but we don't deserve to get crapped on either.  We were balanced compared to what other classes were, not what they will become. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ul0z.showPublicProfile?language=EN>L0z</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/lozdarogue/Rbsmall.JPG BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10> at: 2/26/01 8:45:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=cylant>Cylant</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/26/01 10:34:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2090.topic&index=57>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Talk Item List - Absor</span><hr size=1> to say it frankly.. i think all we really wanted was something new and fun to screw around with.  I think that's all most classes wanted.  Most classes got that.  I guess rogues arent most classes =\ <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udeishan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deishan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/27/01 3:36:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2090.topic&index=58>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.c-cyber.com/CCyber/Samanea/SamaneaThumb.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogue Talk Item List - Absor</span><hr size=1> Sad but what loz said is true.<br>
