We really did get cool stuffs and good improvements, but not as much as others. It's really a great thing hybrids get disciplines, but the way I saw it, Velious brought us, monks and warriors nothing new in the abilities department. i don't count the fearless and resist discipline, because they are just toys for the lower levels to play with, as if to say, 'see? we gave you stuff before level 50'. It would have been nice to add something that really fits our class. What about some discipline that allow us to pick pocket magic items (but not nodrop) of mobs? with a high reuse time and it wouldn't work on some mobs? or one that would allow us to sneak and hide even past see invis mobs? That would belong only to us. I'm sure we could find other stuff like that, and I don't think it is that unbalancing. It all depends on the reuse time and the time it would last.<br>
